name: ffmpeg
description: A library to decode, encode, transcode, mux, demux, stream, filter and play pretty much anything that humans and machines have created.

FFmpeg is the leading multimedia framework, able to decode, encode, transcode, mux, demux, stream, filter and play pretty much anything that humans and machines have created. It supports the most obscure ancient formats up to the cutting edge. No matter if they were designed by some standards committee, the community or a corporation. It is also highly portable: FFmpeg compiles, runs, and passes our testing infrastructure FATE across Linux, Mac OS X, Microsoft Windows, the BSDs, Solaris, etc. under a wide variety of build environments, machine architectures, and configurations.

all.description: Build with all allowed dependencies selected that are compatible with the lgpl license

all-gpl.description: Build with all allowed dependencies selected that are compatible with the gpl license

all-nonfree.description: Build with all allowed dependencies selected with a non-redistributable license

aom.description: AV1 video encoding/decoding via libaom support in ffmpeg

ass.description: Libass subtitles rendering, needed for subtitles and ass filter support in ffmpeg

fdk-aac.description: AAC de/encoding via libfdk-aac, **including GPL-incompatible patent-encumbered HE-AAC**. If you do not require HE-AAC, use the built-in FFmpeg AAC codec.

gpl.description: Allow use of GPL code, the resulting libs and binaries will be under GPL

nonfree.description: Allow use of nonfree code, the resulting libs and binaries will be unredistributable

openssl.description: Needed for https support if gnutls, libtls or mbedtls is not used

snappy.description: Snappy compression, needed for hap encoding

tensorflow.description: TensorFlow as a DNN module backend for DNN based filters like sr

vorbis.description: Vorbis en/decoding via libvorbis, native implementation exists

vpx.description: VP8 and VP9 de/encoding via libvpx

xml2.description: XML parsing using the C library libxml2, needed for dash demuxing support

tsc-base.description: The base set of features for all TSC FFmpeg builds

tsc-desktop-base.description: The base set of features for all TSC desktop FFmpeg builds

tsc-desktop-win.description: The base set of features for all TSC desktop builds for windows

tsc-desktop-mac.description: The base set of features for all TSC desktop builds for mac

tsc-wasm-base.description: The base set of features for all TSC wasm builds

tsc-wasm-image2video.description: The set of features for the image to video microapp

image2.description: Enable muxing and demuxing images with image2
